Difference between array and vector:

Arrays and Vectors are vastly different, yet also functionally similar, and each 
have their own weaknesses and strenghts. With an array, for example, the static 
nature of them allows a lot of easy calculational shortcuts, such as just using the
 integer 10 for a fixed list of 10 items, rather than constantly needing to retreive
 the number of values. Yet using vectors instead of arrays allows for much greater 
 flexibility, for a wide variety of sitations where a dataset can change in size. 
 This increased functionality comes at a price though, as they can be more 
 compliated than a simple array. Thankfully, there are different syntaxes that can 
 be used to easily append or remove values from a vector, and the complexity isnt a 
 super steep hill to overcome. They are considered higher level, so they need a 
 higher level of understanding to work with, but when done right, can be an 
 increcibly poweful tool for a variety of programming situations. They are slightly 
 slower, but just slightly, and the benefits far outweigh the costs in my opinion.
 